Add persistent memory system for agent

Implements a project-scoped memory system that stores memories as markdown
files with YAML frontmatter in ~/.agent_memory/<project_hash>/.

## Core features
- Memory dataclass (name, description, type, content, timestamps)
- Four memory types: user, feedback, project, reference
- Frontmatter parser (manual YAML subset, no dependencies)
- Project-specific directories using SHA-256 hash of cwd
- Auto-loads up to MEMORY_MAX_LOAD memories into system prompt
- Type-based priority sorting (feedback > user > project > reference)

## New tools
- save_memory: validates inputs, preserves created timestamp on updates
- list_memories: returns formatted list of all project memories

## Configuration
- MEMORY_DIR: base directory (default: ~/.agent_memory)
- MEMORY_ENABLED: toggle memory loading (default: True)
- MEMORY_MAX_LOAD: max memories in prompt (default: 10)

## Tests
- 9 tests for memory.py (parse, save, load, project dir)
- 5 tests for memory tools (save, update, list, validation)
- 4 tests for prompt integration (loading, sorting, max_load)
- All tests use tmp_path for isolation

## Cross-architecture support
Works across all architectures (reactive, orchestrator-worker, evaluator-optimizer,
planner-executor) because memories are loaded in build_system_prompt() and all
architectures receive the same RunContext with the populated system prompt.

